Terminalia tomentosa

    Authority   W. & A.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Myrtales:Combretaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 10356

   Notes
   SOURCES
   Troup R 1921 pp 514-529 [USE, DRA, DEP, TEMP, RAIN, DEP, FER, TEXT,
   LIG]
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial deciduous tree.
   COMMON NAMES
   Sain ain, Saj, Asna, Asan, Matti, Sadada, Maddi, Nallamaddi, Karra
   marda, Taukkyan.
   FURTHER INF
   Found at elevations up to 1300 m, growing up to 35 m tall. The tree
   also grows on poor shallow soils, and under many other conditions but
   then it often remains stunted.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
